Therefore, unfortunately, it may be Deja Vu all over again in 2024, with no election integrity, checks and balances, and therefore a disputed election. Given what transpired in 2020, and with 4 YEARS to fix it, it's sad that nothing has been done so that the election process is secure and can be trusted. Drop boxes for example, still allow for fraud. With all of the authentication, two-factor ID systems, etc., that we use regularly for banking apps, etc., you would think the election process could be secured.
